text: I really hate it when people, who had something good happen to them, continue to complain that the good thing doesn’t keep happening to them.
It’s just an incredibly self centered way of thinking.
Angelo, it's 7 am on a Saturday.
Are you allowed to have a mood this early?
That’s the problem
Lol
I shouldn’t be waking up to feeling this way :rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:
You bring up a good point though, I have been a bit thin-skinned lately. Perhaps it’s some time for a self reflection.
Oh?
I was just making a joke
No, I know, but it may have something to it. I’m being serious.
I’m not usually so moody, but I have been (at least online) over the past few weeks. I should probably try and figure that out
Hm. I hadn't really noticed
I feel like I’ve been, but I’m glad it may not have been entirely noticeable :eyes:
Mood is in the tone and sarcasm family of written communication

It’s probably a combination of just being frustrated with large issues I see everyday in the greater span f things, my new schedule of getting up at 4 in the morning, working two jobs, writing, and then when I see people complaining about being fortunate, or stupid things, it’s that little push that gets me moody.
That’s deep.

Like, just think about all the complaints I posted in here just over the past two weeks of spoiler season :sweat_smile:
You might just want to exercise the mute button more liberally. Voluntarily having negativity surrounding your media is a very fixable issue I think.

It doesn't drop their follower count, and you won't see stuff they comment on
